As a French, that' something I had difficulties to assimilate, but now I know that the word "serie" doesn't exist in English (rechecked with Merriam-Webster...), it is an invariant name "series" (not very practical for programming purpose, we have to make seriesList instead of using a plural name, etc.).

Exploring the new, beta feature of adding charts to Excel worksheets, I stumble upon a class:

/**
 * Represents a line chart serie.
 *
 * @author Martin Andersson
 */
@Beta
public interface LineChartSerie extends ChartSerie {
...
}

While it is in beta state, I suggest to rename them to ChartSeries and LineChartSeries.
